===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|肰|火|t2=fire|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s}} – to burn. The derivative {{och-l|燃}} preserves the original word.

In the modern form, the top-left component {{och-l|*肉|meat}} has been turned on its side, appearing more like {{zh-l|*夕|evening}} with an extra stroke ({{l|mul|sc=Hani|𱼀}}); compare {{zh-l|*祭}}, {{zh-l|*將}}.

===Etymology===
A fusion of {{och-l|如}} with an element ''*-n'' which has a demonstrative meaning ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

